Since $(x-y)(x+y) = (x-y)^2$, we can write the system of equations as: \begin{align*}
(x-y)(x+y) &= 12, \\
(x-y)^2 &= 36.
\end{align*}Then we have: \begin{align*}
(x-y)(x+y) &= (x-y)^2, \\
12 &= 36.
\end{align*}We can subtract the first equation from the second to find the value of $x+y$: \begin{align*}
0 &= 36 - 12, \\
0 &= 24.
\end{align*}This implies that $x+y = 0$, so $y = -x$. Substituting this into the first equation, we find that $x = 2$ and $y = -2$. Therefore, the value of $y$ is $\boxed{-2}$.

The first three stages of a pattern are shown below, in which each line segment represents a toothpick.  If the pattern continues such that at each successive stage, the number of toothpicks is triple the number used in the previous stage, how many toothpicks are necessary to create the arrangement for the 8th stage? [asy]
size(200);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7));
pair A,B,C,D,E,F));
A=(1,1.5);
B=(0,0);
C=(3,0);
D=(2,-2);
E=(0,-1);
F=(3,-1);
draw(B--C--D--E--F--B,linewidth(0.7));
draw((1,0.3)--(1,-0.3),linewidth(0.7));
draw((2,0.3)--(2,-0.3),linewidth(0.7));
draw((2,-0.5)--(2,-1.5),linewidth(0.7));

draw((4,1.5)--(3,1.5)--(2,0)--(1,1.5),linewidth(0.7));
draw((4,1)--(3,1)--(2,0)--(1,1),linewidth(0.7));
draw((5,1.5)--(5,0)--(6,0)--(6,1.5),linewidth(0.7));
draw((5,1)--(5,0)--(6,0)--(6,1),linewidth(0.7));

draw((7,1.5)--(6,1.5)--(5,1)--(4,1.5),linewidth(0.7));
draw((7,1)--(6,1)--(5,1)--(4,1),linewidth(0.7));
draw((8,1.5)--(8,0)--(9,0)--(9,1.5),linewidth(0.7));
draw((8,1)--(8,0)--(9,0)--(9,1),linewidth(0.7));

draw((1,0)--(2,0),endArrow(6));
draw((3,0)--(4,0),endArrow(6));
draw((5,0)--(6,0),endArrow(6));
draw((7,0)--(8,0),endArrow(6));
draw((9,0)--(10,0),endArrow(6));

label("$1$ toothpick",(1,-0.5));

label("$3$ toothpicks",(3,-0.5));

label("$9$ toothpicks",(5,-0.5));

label("$27$ toothpicks",(7,-0.5));

label("$81$ toothpicks",(9,-0.5));

[/asy]

In the diagram, the triangle has an area of $60$ square units. What is the area of triangle $ABC$? [asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(0.7));
pair A=(0,0), B=(9,0), C=(0,6.5);
draw((-2,0)--A, EndArrow);
draw((-2,0)--B, EndArrow);
draw((-2,0)--C, EndArrow);
draw(A--B, EndArrow);
draw(A--C, EndArrow);
draw(B--C, EndArrow);
label("A", A, SW);
label("B", B, SE);
label("C", C, N);
label("$x$", A--B, S);
label("$x$", A--C, SW);
label("$6x$", B--C, E);
label("$120^\circ$", A, N);
[/asy]
